<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName LSID="666B05B5-C5E8-5E3B-8C20-3C32A9B2E128" authority="(Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382 (1926)." authorityName="Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">Melanconis marginalis (Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382 (1926).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
This species is here subdivided into four subspecies below. See under subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="subsp. marginalis (Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="subsp. marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="marginalis">marginalis</taxonomicName>
for the original species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="Papers from the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="377 - 396" refId="B62" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1926a. Cultural life-histories of Diaporthe. I. Papers from the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters 6: 377 - 396" title="Cultural life-histories of Diaporthe. I." volume="6" year="1926 a">Wehmeyer (1926a)</bibRefCitation>
combined 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1887" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Diaporthe marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 115" authorityYear="1863" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he later (
<bibRefCitation author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B64" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1941. A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania. University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series 14: 1 - 161" title="A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania." volume="14" year="1941">Wehmeyer 1941</bibRefCitation>
) argued that the conidia only differ from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in depth of pigmentation and, therefore, reduced 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a subspecies of the latter. In Europe, where, owing to 
<bibRefCitation author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B64" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1941. A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania. University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series 14: 1 - 161" title="A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania." volume="14" year="1941">Wehmeyer (1941)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 115" authorityYear="1863" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alnus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Alnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was always identified as 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrak, F" journalOrPublisher="Annales Mycologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="251 - 349" refId="B32" refString="Petrak, F, 1941. Mykologische Notizen. Annales Mycologici 39: 251 - 349" title="Mykologische Notizen." volume="39" year="1941">Petrak (1941)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium dimorphum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time, described both conidial types, but still found it probable that 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium dimorphum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was an abnormal form of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. sphaeroideum" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="sphaeroideum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. sphaeroideum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the putative name of the asexual morph of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi, T" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Government Forest Experimental Station Meguro" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 242" refId="B24" refString="Kobayashi, T, 1970. Taxonomic studies of Japanese Diaporthaceae with special reference to their life-histories. Bulletin of the Government Forest Experimental Station Meguro 226: 1 - 242" title="Taxonomic studies of Japanese Diaporthaceae with special reference to their life-histories." volume="226" year="1970">Kobayashi (1970)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jensen, JD" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B21" refString="Jensen, JD, 1984. Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho. Mycotaxon 20: 275 - 281" title="Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho." volume="20" year="1984">Jensen (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, however, were convinced that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a species separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is here confirmed phylogenetically. In addition, ascospores of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are narrower, usually more oblong and symmetric than those of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and appendages shorter, stouter and rounded or truncate at the ends, which swell and become diffuse in mounts.
</paragraph>
